<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-08-09T08:24:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-08-09T08:24:00-05:00" n="775" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d775">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">860n.00/7: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Commissioner at Riga</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Young</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Riga</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-08-09T15:00:00+01:36"><hi rend="italic">August 9,
                                            1920—3 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received August 9—2:52
                                    p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                            <p>99. In view of general situation Baltic Provinces I strongly urge
                                American naval vessel, preferably destroyer, be despatched Baltic
                                waters. This recommendation concurred in by military attache [is
                                made] only after most careful study and consideration of entire
                                situation.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Young</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>